details.description: Here at Your Mom's Donuts, we're not about ordinary. We aren't about a stale chocolate donut with sprinkles. We don't believe preservatives or artificial colors belong in donuts. We don't believe that donuts should be produced on an assembly line. We think every donut should be a masterpiece. We think supporting local farms is cool. We think bringing you donuts that are filled with quality ingredients is even cooler. We think words like "bliss" and "heavenly" should come to mind when you bite into one of our donuts. We think your mouth will agree.

Hi Vincent, we are sorry that we were out of donuts when you made it to our flagship location in Matthews. That is where we bake every donut fresh each morning, for all three of our shops. Each donut is made by hand with a two-day process of making the dough, letting it proof for 48 hours, and then frying them in the wee hours of the morning the day that it will be sold. We do take pre-orders, partly because as a small business that helps us gauge the number of donuts we need to make each day, and reduce waste. Plus, it ensures to customers that they will get the donut they want if they know they can’t get to our shop within the first couple hours after we open. We hope that clears up any confusion, and hope you’ll come by the shop again to try our craft donuts.
Thanks,
Courtney

After everyone in the store had finished ordering, the spry old man walked up to the counter and ordered one donut. ONE donut. Fake location: reheat/delivery location only. This is apparently not an actual bakery but rather a resale location for reheated goods. According to the clerk, they don't make their donuts but get them delivered from the Monroe, NC store. Was there at 11am on a Saturday and the only donuts they had were a cancelled order of "minis" that had been delivered earlier from the main location in Monroe and not picked up. Clerk would not tell me if they were fresh from this morning...she was "unsure" (which made think they were at least a day stale). Waiting for something fresh was not an option because there were no plans to make more...because they apparently can't..a truck drops them off.

I'm all for supporting local business but this one seems it isn't an actual bakery...but rather a reheat-and-serve satellite for the Monroe, NC location off Hayne St..I drove 20 minutes with some very excited kids in the car only to see Costco resale items and NO DONUTS. Very sad kiddos = very mad dad.

Long story short: they are a donut shop that was out of donuts and said they were not making any more...clerk just shrugged. Will not return.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Vincent, we are sorry that we were out of donuts when you made it to our flagship location in Matthews. That is where we bake every donut fresh each morning, for all three of our shops. Each donut is made by hand with a two-day process of making the dough, letting it proof for 48 hours, and then frying them in the wee hours of the morning the day that it will be sold. We do take pre-orders, partly because as a small business that helps us gauge the number of donuts we need to make each day, and reduce waste. Plus, it ensures to customers that they will get the donut they want if they know they can’t get to our shop within the first couple hours after we open. We hope that clears up any confusion, and hope you’ll come by the shop again to try our craft donuts.
Thanks,
Courtney
